Notice of any hearing scheduled by this Administration shall state:
The date, time, place, and nature of the hearing;
The legal authority and jurisdiction of the Administration to hear the matter;
The facts in sufficient detail to enable a party to prepare his case;
The nature of the proposed action that the Administration is to consider;
The right of a party to call witnesses and offer documentary evidence under the provisions of § 10-213 of the State Government Article;
When applicable, the right of a party to request the subpoena of witnesses and the costs thereof;
That a copy of the hearing procedures is available on request of a party, and the cost to obtain a copy;
The right of a party to the hearing to be represented by counsel; and
If a licensee is a party to the hearing, the right of the Administration, on failure of the licensee to appear, to:
Order a suspension of the party's license or privilege until the party appears for a hearing; or
Impose any sanction proposed in the notice.
